{"word":"H3418 - יֶרֶק - yereq - yeh'-rek - Grass","slug":"H3418","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יֶרֶק</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yereq"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yeh'-rek"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Grass"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E8;&#x05E7; - yereq</b> - <i>yeh'-rek</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H3417\">H3417</a> (in the sense of <i>vacuity</i> of color); properly <i>pallor</i>, that is, hence the yellowish <i>green</i> of young and sickly vegetation; concretely <i>verdure</i>, that is, grass or vegetation: - grass, green (thing)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3387\">H3387</a>, <a href=\"#/H3419\">H3419</a>, <a href=\"#/H3420\">H3420</a>, <a href=\"#/H3421\">H3421</a>, <a href=\"#/H3422\">H3422</a>"}]}